        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="455" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d455">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Hopkins Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Presidents Special Assistant</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Hopkins</hi>) <hi rend="italic">to the President</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d455fn1">The relationship of this note to the Seventh
                        Plenary Meeting appears from internal evidence and from Sherwood, pp. 860,
                        861-862. See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_902">p.
                        902</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Yalta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-10">February 10,
                            1945</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. <persName>President</persName>
                    </hi> The Russians have given in so much at this conference that I don’t think
                    we should let them down. Let the British disagree if they want to—and continue
                    their disagreement at Moscow. Simply say it is all referred to the Reparations
                    Commission with the minutes to show the British disagree about any mention of
                    the 10 billion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WHD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harry</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
